FBIS3-25365 "drafr032_b_94001" FBIS-AFR-94-032 Document Type:Daily Report 16 Feb 1994 EAST AFRICA Somalia Italian Defense Minister Says Hostages Released LD1502125994 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1137 GMT 15 Feb 94 LD1502125994 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext Language: Italian Article Type:BFN [Text] The two Italians held hostage in Somalia since last Saturday [12 February] were released this morning. The information was released by Defense Minister Fabio Fabbri. The two men, Gianfranco Stefani and Sergio Passadore, are currently on their way to Mogadishu by helicopter. It is yet known whether the $50,000 ransom demanded by the kidnappers was paid.
